Fearless Floating- BJ
Grades: 2, 3, 4, 5

Are you ready to go on an engineering adventure? Explore new places with Flynn as she travels around the world lending a hand! Flynn needs your help solving problems as they pop up, and helping her get out of trouble by putting your engineering intuition to the test! On this adventure, Flynn has decided to make her way down the Amazon River to meet her family. She needs a device that will make it down the treacherous rapids and keep water and critters out during her journey. Can you help her make her way safely back to her parents? Fun patch included.

*This event is for 2016 registered Girl Scouts, and registered & approved adult volunteers.
* For safety and supervision reasons, troops and individuals are not permitted to bring non-Girl Scouts or siblings. 
*Girl/adult ratios must be followed and adults are expected to stay on the premises during the event. 

$35/girl, $1/adult
Contact: Brittany McCallister 904.389.3071
